pageContext.description: Part of a socket rim, embedded with other metal in the socket of this celt.,The decoration is very faint & encrusted over on other side. Except for the small hole thro' loop, it is solid, as though from a faulty mould. Cast marks are most prominent!
pageContext.patina: sea green on one side - on the other the patina is nearly covered with a rough, green encrustment.
pageContext.surface: on one side, fairly smooth & a little pitted. Traces of light earth. (Varnished all over)
pageContext.associations: One of a Bronze Founder's Hoard:- 4 Socketed Celts, Lump of Metal, part of a chisel or gouge socket, Edge of a Socketed Celt, & part of a spearhead.
pageContext.collection: Colchester Museum,presented to Essex Arch. Soc. by Mr W.H. King,(1889.94 Price Cat),(Stick on label:- "Royal Arch. Inst 62")
